message:
Testing on real handset (Lg Optimus L9) reveals that:
- at least one of the action menu items must be visible at start, if not then action bar is disabled completely;
- Intent.createChooser() is uglier than simple intent.

Async task returns Result type now.

At this time some strange behaviour is observed:
- ResultFragment has one instance is NetCat (asynctask wrapper);
- this NetCat instance fires off asynctasks on every execute() method call;
- it works great when executing CONNECT and RECEIVE operations;
- RECEIVE op is blocking, but is should only block corresponding asynctask thread;
- but in my case it blocks whole NetCat instance, so new operations doesn't pass to execute() method;
- they only start executing after other side is terminated, connection is closed and RECEIVE op is completed.
